課程概述 Course Description
       課程將包括以下主題: 數值方法求解流體控制方程式；離散化技術和解決算法；有限差分求解古典波動相關方程式模型，以及擴散現象和平衡；Von-Neumann穩定性分析；網格生成；以及不可壓縮 Navier - Stokes方程式的應用。The course will cover the following topics: Numerical methods for solving the governing equation of fluid flows; Discretization techniques and solution algorithms; Finite difference solutions to classical model equations pertinent to wave phenomena, diffusion phenomena and equilibrium; von-Neumann stability analysis; Grid generation; Applications to the incompressible Navier-Stokes equations.    

課程學習目標 Course Objectives    
	    The purpose of this course is to teach students how to solve fluid mechanics problems numerically.  Students are asked to write computer programs to simulate fluid flows.  Once students are able to implement numerical methods to computer programs, they are also expected to use commercial software to simulate fluid flow problems without difficulty.    

課程進度 Course Outline


週次 Week進度說明 Progress Description
1Introduction to Computational Fluid Dynamics2Classification of Partial Differential Equations3Classification of Partial Differential Equations4Classification of Partial Differential Equations5Discretization Techniques6Discretization Techniques7Discretization Techniques8Consistency, Stability and Convergence9Consistency, Stability and Convergence10Methods of Solving Parabolic, Elleiptic and Hyperbolic Equations 11Methods of Solving Parabolic, Elleiptic and Hyperbolic Equations 12Methods of Solving Parabolic, Elleiptic and Hyperbolic Equations 13Conservation-Element and Solution Element (CESE) method14Conservation-Element and Solution Element (CESE) method15Incompressible Navier-Stokes Equations16Incompressible Navier-Stokes Equations17Grid Generation18Final Exam 

